### Behavior Overview
- Blog post slugs are derived from the MDX filename (no directory nesting). See `getBlogPosts()` in [utils](mdc:app/blog/utils.ts).
- Frontmatter is mandatory in each MDX post: `title`, `publishedAt`, `summary`, optional `image`.
- If a post omits `image`, the OG image is generated from `app/og/route.tsx` using the post title.
- `baseUrl` in `app/sitemap.ts` is the canonical origin used across metadata, sitemap, and RSS.
